<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="124" pageId="1" pageNumber="123" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1451,2029,2092]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,159,291]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="124" pageId="1" pageNumber="123">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bhattacharjee, R." box="[296,537,2029,2055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="123" pagination="199 - 262" refId="ref1680" refString="Bhattacharjee, R. (1982) Stachys L. In: Davis, P. H. (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands, vol. 7. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, pp. 199 - 262." type="book chapter" year="1982">Bhattacharjee (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, in 
<collectingCountry box="[583,663,2029,2055]" name="Turkey" pageId="1" pageNumber="123">Turkey</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montbret &amp; Aucher ex Bentham, K" authorityYear="1836" box="[673,863,2029,2055]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Stachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subnuda">
<emphasis box="[673,863,2029,2055]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="123">Stachys subnuda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed only in two provinces, 
<collectingRegion box="[1301,1401,2029,2055]" country="Turkey" name="Erzincan" pageId="1" pageNumber="123">Erzincan</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[136,230,2065,2091]" country="Turkey" name="Hakkari" pageId="1" pageNumber="123">Hakkari</collectingRegion>
. 
<collectorName box="[239,306,2065,2091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="123">These</collectorName>
two provinces are very far from each other. 
<typeStatus box="[799,855,2066,2092]" pageId="1" pageNumber="123">Type</typeStatus>
location 
<collectingRegion box="[958,1058,2065,2091]" country="Turkey" name="Erzincan" pageId="1" pageNumber="123">Erzincan</collectingRegion>
is not geographically similar to the location 
<collectingRegion box="[230,319,159,183]" country="Turkey" name="Hakkari" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Hakkari</collectingRegion>
. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:04408785AC515200FE9BFD6AD9B5FEDB:89366048AC525200FF58FF6DDB3BFF4F" box="[331,372,159,183]" country="Turkey" municipality="Southeast" name="The" pageId="2" pageNumber="124" stateProvince="Erzincan">The</location>
plants, growing in 
<collectingRegion box="[585,775,159,183]" country="Turkey" name="Hakkari" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Hakkari province</collectingRegion>
, might not be 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montbret &amp; Aucher ex Bentham, K" authorityYear="1836" box="[934,1052,159,183]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Stachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subnuda">
<emphasis box="[934,1052,159,183]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">S. subnuda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and might be 
<taxonomicName authority="Boissier &amp; Hohenacker" authorityName="Boissier &amp; Hohenacker" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Stachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kurdica">
<emphasis box="[1218,1326,159,183]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">S. kurdica</emphasis>
Boissier &amp; Hohenacker
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Boissier, P. E." box="[308,497,195,219]" pageId="2" pageNumber="124" refId="ref1727" refString="Boissier, P. E. (1844) Diagnoses plantarum orientalium novarum, vol. 5. Ducloux, Paris, 92 pp. [https: // archive. org / details / bub _ gb _ 8 z 0 - AAAAcAAJ / page / n 29 / mode / 2 up]" type="book" year="1844">Boissier 1844: 31</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[518,687,195,219]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Stachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kurdica">
<emphasis box="[518,687,195,219]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Stachys kurdica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in 
<collectingRegion box="[867,953,195,219]" country="Turkey" name="Hakkari" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Hakkari</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1004,1074,195,219]" country="Turkey" name="Sirnak" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Şırnak</collectingRegion>
provinces of 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1220,1324,195,219]" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Southeast</collectingMunicipality>
<collectingCountry box="[1330,1406,195,219]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[232,275,232,255]" name="Iraq" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Iraq</collectingCountry>
and also extends to 
<collectingCountry box="[489,532,232,255]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Guner, O. &amp; Selvi, S. &amp; Altinordu, F. &amp; Martin, E." box="[545,736,231,255]" pageId="2" pageNumber="124" pagination="271 - 280" refId="ref1922" refString="Guner, O., Selvi, S., Altinordu, F. &amp; Martin, E. (2019) The analysis of some biological data on Stachys kurdica (Lamiaceae) in Turkey. Phytologia Balcanica 25 (3): 271 - 280. https: // doi. org / 10.3906 / bot- 2010 - 12" type="journal article" year="2019">
Güner 
<emphasis box="[619,666,231,255]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Montbret &amp; Aucher ex Bentham, K" authorityYear="1836" box="[818,934,231,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Stachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subnuda">
<emphasis box="[818,934,231,255]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">S. subnuda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, having two populations in 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:04408785AC515200FE9BFD6AD9B5FEDB:89366048AC525200FADEFF15DFC0FF07" box="[1229,1423,231,255]" country="Turkey" name="Erzincan province" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Erzincan province</location>
of Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[222,298,267,291]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Turkey</collectingCountry>
which are close to each other, a narrow endemic species to 
<collectingCountry box="[936,1014,267,291]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="124">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
